{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":723,"text":"So let me ask for a show of hands."},{"time":2899,"text":"How many people here are over the age of 48?"},{"time":7091,"text":"Well, there do seem to be a few."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9972,"text":"Well, congratulations,"},{"time":12147,"text":"because if you look at this particular slide of U.S. life expectancy,"},{"time":16017,"text":"you are now in excess of the average life span"},{"time":19115,"text":"of somebody who was born in 1900."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21902,"text":"But look what happened in the course of that century."},{"time":25436,"text":"If you follow that curve,"},{"time":27098,"text":"you'll see that it starts way down there."},{"time":29712,"text":"There's that dip there for the 1918 flu."},{"time":32181,"text":"And here we are at 2010,"},{"time":34603,"text":"average life expectancy of a child born today, age 79,"},{"time":37659,"text":"and we are not done yet."},{"time":39555,"text":"Now, that's the good news."},{"time":40890,"text":"But there's still a lot of work to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42731,"text":"So, for instance, if you ask,"},{"time":44365,"text":"how many diseases do we now know"},{"time":47091,"text":"the exact molecular basis?"},{"time":49150,"text":"Turns out it's about 4,000, which is pretty amazing,"},{"time":52708,"text":"because most of those molecular discoveries"},{"time":54944,"text":"have just happened in the last little while."},{"time":57609,"text":"It's exciting to see that in terms of what we've learned,"},{"time":60905,"text":"but how many of those 4,000 diseases"},{"time":63012,"text":"now have treatments available?"},{"time":65360,"text":"Only about 250."},{"time":67248,"text":"So we have this huge challenge, this huge gap."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70006,"text":"You would think this wouldn't be too hard,"},{"time":72586,"text":"that we would simply have the ability"},{"time":74112,"text":"to take this fundamental information that we're learning"},{"time":77138,"text":"about how it is that basic biology teaches us"},{"time":80283,"text":"about the causes of disease"},{"time":82185,"text":"and build a bridge across this yawning gap"},{"time":85211,"text":"between what we've learned about basic science"},{"time":87591,"text":"and its application,"},{"time":89086,"text":"a bridge that would look maybe something like this,"},{"time":92343,"text":"where you'd have to put together a nice shiny way"},{"time":95955,"text":"to get from one side to the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98923,"text":"Well, wouldn't it be nice if it was that easy?"},{"time":101523,"text":"Unfortunately, it's not."},{"time":103668,"text":"In reality, trying to go from fundamental knowledge"},{"time":106259,"text":"to its application is more like this."},{"time":108923,"text":"There are no shiny bridges."},{"time":110838,"text":"You sort of place your bets."},{"time":112490,"text":"Maybe you've got a swimmer and a rowboat"},{"time":114451,"text":"and a sailboat and a tugboat"},{"time":115975,"text":"and you set them off on their way,"},{"time":117703,"text":"and the rains come and the lightning flashes,"},{"time":120367,"text":"and oh my gosh, there are sharks in the water"},{"time":121881,"text":"and the swimmer gets into trouble,"},{"time":123902,"text":"and, uh oh, the swimmer drowned"},{"time":125486,"text":"and the sailboat capsized,"},{"time":128698,"text":"and that tugboat, well, it hit the rocks,"},{"time":130399,"text":"and maybe if you're lucky, somebody gets across."}]},{"cues":[{"time":133039,"text":"Well, what does this really look like?"},{"time":135028,"text":"Well, what is it to make a therapeutic, anyway?"},{"time":137082,"text":"What's a drug? A drug is made up"},{"time":140083,"text":"of a small molecule of hydrogen, carbon,"},{"time":142408,"text":"oxygen, nitrogen, and a few other atoms"},{"time":144659,"text":"all cobbled together in a shape,"},{"time":146882,"text":"and it's those shapes that determine whether, in fact,"},{"time":149259,"text":"that particular drug is going to hit its target."},{"time":152572,"text":"Is it going to land where it's supposed to?"},{"time":154795,"text":"So look at this picture here -- a lot of shapes dancing around for you."},{"time":157951,"text":"Now what you need to do, if you're trying to develop"},{"time":160338,"text":"a new treatment for autism"},{"time":161795,"text":"or Alzheimer's disease or cancer"},{"time":164014,"text":"is to find the right shape in that mix"},{"time":165806,"text":"that will ultimately provide benefit and will be safe."},{"time":168723,"text":"And when you look at what happens to that pipeline,"},{"time":171890,"text":"you start out maybe with thousands,"},{"time":173391,"text":"tens of thousands of compounds."},{"time":175033,"text":"You weed down through various steps"},{"time":177182,"text":"that cause many of these to fail."},{"time":178565,"text":"Ultimately, maybe you can run a clinical trial with four or five of these,"},{"time":181905,"text":"and if all goes well, 14 years after you started,"},{"time":184947,"text":"you will get one approval."},{"time":186958,"text":"And it will cost you upwards of a billion dollars"},{"time":188988,"text":"for that one success."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191132,"text":"So we have to look at this pipeline the way an engineer would,"},{"time":194436,"text":"and say, \"How can we do better?\""},{"time":195644,"text":"And that's the main theme of what I want to say to you this morning."},{"time":198321,"text":"How can we make this go faster?"},{"time":200134,"text":"How can we make it more successful?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":203199,"text":"Well, let me tell you about a few examples"},{"time":204540,"text":"where this has actually worked."},{"time":206796,"text":"One that has just happened in the last few months"},{"time":209747,"text":"is the successful approval of a drug for cystic fibrosis."},{"time":213457,"text":"But it's taken a long time to get there."},{"time":215111,"text":"Cystic fibrosis had its molecular cause discovered in 1989"},{"time":219713,"text":"by my group working with another group in Toronto,"},{"time":222041,"text":"discovering what the mutation was in a particular gene"},{"time":224176,"text":"on chromosome 7."},{"time":225804,"text":"That picture you see there?"},{"time":227842,"text":"Here it is. That's the same kid."},{"time":229945,"text":"That's Danny Bessette, 23 years later,"},{"time":233289,"text":"because this is the year,"},{"time":234568,"text":"and it's also the year where Danny got married,"},{"time":237006,"text":"where we have, for the first time, the approval by the FDA"},{"time":240063,"text":"of a drug that precisely targets the defect in cystic fibrosis"},{"time":243800,"text":"based upon all this molecular understanding."},{"time":245738,"text":"That's the good news."},{"time":247162,"text":"The bad news is, this drug doesn't actually treat all cases of cystic fibrosis,"},{"time":250791,"text":"and it won't work for Danny, and we're still waiting"},{"time":253000,"text":"for that next generation to help him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255335,"text":"But it took 23 years to get this far. That's too long."},{"time":258530,"text":"How do we go faster?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":260223,"text":"Well, one way to go faster is to take advantage of technology,"},{"time":262921,"text":"and a very important technology that we depend on"},{"time":265585,"text":"for all of this is the human genome,"},{"time":267881,"text":"the ability to be able to look at a chromosome,"},{"time":270469,"text":"to unzip it, to pull out all the DNA,"},{"time":273139,"text":"and to be able to then read out the letters in that DNA code,"},{"time":276089,"text":"the A's, C's, G's and T's"},{"time":278170,"text":"that are our instruction book and the instruction book for all living things,"},{"time":281441,"text":"and the cost of doing this,"},{"time":282955,"text":"which used to be in the hundreds of millions of dollars,"},{"time":285610,"text":"has in the course of the last 10 years"},{"time":287523,"text":"fallen faster than Moore's Law, down to the point"},{"time":289922,"text":"where it is less than 10,000 dollars today to have your genome sequenced, or mine,"},{"time":293929,"text":"and we're headed for the $1,000 genome fairly soon."},{"time":297728,"text":"Well, that's exciting."},{"time":299054,"text":"How does that play out in terms of application to a disease?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302864,"text":"I want to tell you about another disorder."},{"time":305144,"text":"This one is a disorder which is quite rare."},{"time":307456,"text":"It's called Hutchinson-Gilford progeria,"},{"time":310224,"text":"and it is the most dramatic form of premature aging."},{"time":313529,"text":"Only about one in every four million kids has this disease,"},{"time":317312,"text":"and in a simple way, what happens is,"},{"time":320672,"text":"because of a mutation in a particular gene,"},{"time":323373,"text":"a protein is made that's toxic to the cell"},{"time":326040,"text":"and it causes these individuals to age"},{"time":328337,"text":"at about seven times the normal rate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":330921,"text":"Let me show you a video of what that does to the cell."},{"time":334064,"text":"The normal cell, if you looked at it under the microscope,"},{"time":337199,"text":"would have a nucleus sitting in the middle of the cell,"},{"time":340088,"text":"which is nice and round and smooth in its boundaries"},{"time":343967,"text":"and it looks kind of like that."},{"time":345722,"text":"A progeria cell, on the other hand,"},{"time":347586,"text":"because of this toxic protein called progerin,"},{"time":350688,"text":"has these lumps and bumps in it."},{"time":352972,"text":"So what we would like to do after discovering this"},{"time":355987,"text":"back in 2003"},{"time":357839,"text":"is to come up with a way to try to correct that."},{"time":361057,"text":"Well again, by knowing something about the molecular pathways,"},{"time":364145,"text":"it was possible to pick"},{"time":366144,"text":"one of those many, many compounds that might have been useful"},{"time":368761,"text":"and try it out."},{"time":370222,"text":"In an experiment done in cell culture"},{"time":372797,"text":"and shown here in a cartoon,"},{"time":374839,"text":"if you take that particular compound"},{"time":377533,"text":"and you add it to that cell that has progeria,"},{"time":380789,"text":"and you watch to see what happened,"},{"time":383010,"text":"in just 72 hours, that cell becomes,"},{"time":385972,"text":"for all purposes that we can determine,"},{"time":388240,"text":"almost like a normal cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390082,"text":"Well that was exciting, but would it actually work in a real human being?"},{"time":394423,"text":"This has led, in the space of only four years"},{"time":397808,"text":"from the time the gene was discovered to the start of a clinical trial,"},{"time":401309,"text":"to a test of that very compound."},{"time":403506,"text":"And the kids that you see here"},{"time":405469,"text":"all volunteered to be part of this,"},{"time":408031,"text":"28 of them,"},{"time":409492,"text":"and you can see as soon as the picture comes up"},{"time":412587,"text":"that they are in fact a remarkable group of young people"},{"time":415969,"text":"all afflicted by this disease,"},{"time":417388,"text":"all looking quite similar to each other."},{"time":419637,"text":"And instead of telling you more about it,"},{"time":421311,"text":"I'm going to invite one of them, Sam Berns from Boston,"},{"time":425297,"text":"who's here this morning, to come up on the stage"},{"time":427730,"text":"and tell us about his experience"},{"time":429950,"text":"as a child affected with progeria."},{"time":431860,"text":"Sam is 15 years old. His parents, Scott Berns and Leslie Gordon,"},{"time":435918,"text":"both physicians, are here with us this morning as well."},{"time":438039,"text":"Sam, please have a seat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440577,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":447897,"text":"So Sam, why don't you tell these folks"},{"time":450075,"text":"what it's like being affected with this condition called progeria?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":453450,"text":"Sam Burns: Well, progeria limits me in some ways."},{"time":457258,"text":"I cannot play sports or do physical activities,"},{"time":461222,"text":"but I have been able to take interest in things"},{"time":464426,"text":"that progeria, luckily, does not limit."},{"time":467405,"text":"But when there is something that I really do want to do"},{"time":469962,"text":"that progeria gets in the way of, like marching band"},{"time":472979,"text":"or umpiring, we always find a way to do it,"},{"time":476405,"text":"and that just shows that progeria isn't in control of my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479922,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":481632,"text":"Francis Collins: So what would you like to say to researchers"},{"time":483668,"text":"here in the auditorium and others listening to this?"},{"time":486765,"text":"What would you say to them both about research on progeria"},{"time":489362,"text":"and maybe about other conditions as well?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":491248,"text":"SB: Well, research on progeria has come so far"},{"time":494394,"text":"in less than 15 years,"},{"time":496636,"text":"and that just shows the drive that researchers can have"},{"time":501005,"text":"to get this far, and it really means a lot"},{"time":504423,"text":"to myself and other kids with progeria,"},{"time":507674,"text":"and it shows that if that drive exists,"},{"time":510498,"text":"anybody can cure any disease,"},{"time":513099,"text":"and hopefully progeria can be cured in the near future,"},{"time":517046,"text":"and so we can eliminate those 4,000 diseases"},{"time":520803,"text":"that Francis was talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":523810,"text":"FC: Excellent. So Sam took the day off from school today"},{"time":526939,"text":"to be here, and he is — (Applause) --"},{"time":532074,"text":"He is, by the way, a straight-A+ student in the ninth grade"},{"time":536890,"text":"in his school in Boston."},{"time":538223,"text":"Please join me in thanking and welcoming Sam."},{"time":540424,"text":"SB: Thank you very much. FC: Well done. Well done, buddy."},{"time":544077,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":556886,"text":"So I just want to say a couple more things"},{"time":558602,"text":"about that particular story, and then try to generalize"},{"time":561734,"text":"how could we have stories of success"},{"time":564230,"text":"all over the place for these diseases, as Sam says,"},{"time":567743,"text":"these 4,000 that are waiting for answers."},{"time":570262,"text":"You might have noticed that the drug"},{"time":572134,"text":"that is now in clinical trial for progeria"},{"time":574903,"text":"is not a drug that was designed for that."},{"time":576667,"text":"It's such a rare disease, it would be hard for a company"},{"time":579529,"text":"to justify spending hundreds of millions of dollars to generate a drug."},{"time":583259,"text":"This is a drug that was developed for cancer."},{"time":585419,"text":"Turned out, it didn't work very well for cancer,"},{"time":587584,"text":"but it has exactly the right properties, the right shape,"},{"time":589907,"text":"to work for progeria, and that's what's happened."},{"time":592799,"text":"Wouldn't it be great if we could do that more systematically?"},{"time":596027,"text":"Could we, in fact, encourage all the companies that are out there"},{"time":599823,"text":"that have drugs in their freezers"},{"time":601661,"text":"that are known to be safe in humans"},{"time":603863,"text":"but have never actually succeeded in terms"},{"time":606155,"text":"of being effective for the treatments they were tried for?"},{"time":609011,"text":"Now we're learning about all these new molecular pathways --"},{"time":611395,"text":"some of those could be repositioned or repurposed,"},{"time":614474,"text":"or whatever word you want to use, for new applications,"},{"time":616873,"text":"basically teaching old drugs new tricks."},{"time":619842,"text":"That could be a phenomenal, valuable activity."},{"time":622529,"text":"We have many discussions now between NIH and companies"},{"time":625575,"text":"about doing this that are looking very promising."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627699,"text":"And you could expect quite a lot to come from this."},{"time":630313,"text":"There are quite a number of success stories one can point to"},{"time":633352,"text":"about how this has led to major advances."},{"time":635705,"text":"The first drug for HIV/AIDS"},{"time":637912,"text":"was not developed for HIV/AIDS."},{"time":639641,"text":"It was developed for cancer. It was AZT."},{"time":642159,"text":"It didn't work very well for cancer, but became"},{"time":644160,"text":"the first successful antiretroviral,"},{"time":646276,"text":"and you can see from the table there are others as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648848,"text":"So how do we actually make that a more generalizable effort?"},{"time":652492,"text":"Well, we have to come up with a partnership"},{"time":654716,"text":"between academia, government, the private sector,"},{"time":657576,"text":"and patient organizations to make that so."},{"time":660029,"text":"At NIH, we have started this new"},{"time":661679,"text":"National Center for Advancing Translational Sciences."},{"time":664879,"text":"It just started last December, and this is one of its goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":668494,"text":"Let me tell you another thing we could do."},{"time":669935,"text":"Wouldn't it be nice to be able to a test a drug"},{"time":672854,"text":"to see if it's effective and safe"},{"time":675225,"text":"without having to put patients at risk,"},{"time":677326,"text":"because that first time you're never quite sure?"},{"time":679879,"text":"How do we know, for instance, whether drugs are safe"},{"time":682030,"text":"before we give them to people? We test them on animals."},{"time":685275,"text":"And it's not all that reliable, and it's costly,"},{"time":687917,"text":"and it's time-consuming."},{"time":689607,"text":"Suppose we could do this instead on human cells."},{"time":692470,"text":"You probably know, if you've been paying attention"},{"time":694702,"text":"to some of the science literature"},{"time":696002,"text":"that you can now take a skin cell"},{"time":697658,"text":"and encourage it to become a liver cell"},{"time":700539,"text":"or a heart cell or a kidney cell or a brain cell for any of us."},{"time":703614,"text":"So what if you used those cells as your test"},{"time":706766,"text":"for whether a drug is going to work and whether it's going to be safe?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":709711,"text":"Here you see a picture of a lung on a chip."},{"time":713942,"text":"This is something created by the Wyss Institute in Boston,"},{"time":717463,"text":"and what they have done here, if we can run the little video,"},{"time":720638,"text":"is to take cells from an individual,"},{"time":722774,"text":"turn them into the kinds of cells that are present in the lung,"},{"time":725883,"text":"and determine what would happen"},{"time":727688,"text":"if you added to this various drug compounds"},{"time":730765,"text":"to see if they are toxic or safe."},{"time":733230,"text":"You can see this chip even breathes."},{"time":735501,"text":"It has an air channel. It has a blood channel."},{"time":738118,"text":"And it has cells in between"},{"time":739821,"text":"that allow you to see what happens when you add a compound."},{"time":742259,"text":"Are those cells happy or not?"},{"time":744031,"text":"You can do this same kind of chip technology"},{"time":747062,"text":"for kidneys, for hearts, for muscles,"},{"time":749271,"text":"all the places where you want to see whether a drug"},{"time":751735,"text":"is going to be a problem, for the liver."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754016,"text":"And ultimately, because you can do this for the individual,"},{"time":757064,"text":"we could even see this moving to the point"},{"time":759278,"text":"where the ability to develop and test medicines"},{"time":762719,"text":"will be you on a chip, what we're trying to say here is"},{"time":765905,"text":"the individualizing of the process of developing drugs"},{"time":769406,"text":"and testing their safety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":771654,"text":"So let me sum up."},{"time":773306,"text":"We are in a remarkable moment here."},{"time":775566,"text":"For me, at NIH now for almost 20 years,"},{"time":777669,"text":"there has never been a time where there was more excitement"},{"time":780270,"text":"about the potential that lies in front of us."},{"time":782855,"text":"We have made all these discoveries"},{"time":784647,"text":"pouring out of laboratories across the world."},{"time":787012,"text":"What do we need to capitalize on this? First of all, we need resources."},{"time":790374,"text":"This is research that's high-risk, sometimes high-cost."},{"time":793929,"text":"The payoff is enormous, both in terms of health"},{"time":795900,"text":"and in terms of economic growth. We need to support that."},{"time":798780,"text":"Second, we need new kinds of partnerships"},{"time":801081,"text":"between academia and government and the private sector"},{"time":803302,"text":"and patient organizations, just like the one I've been describing here,"},{"time":806649,"text":"in terms of the way in which we could go after repurposing new compounds."},{"time":810229,"text":"And third, and maybe most important, we need talent."},{"time":813465,"text":"We need the best and the brightest"},{"time":815606,"text":"from many different disciplines to come and join this effort --"},{"time":818463,"text":"all ages, all different groups --"},{"time":820909,"text":"because this is the time, folks."},{"time":822996,"text":"This is the 21st-century biology that you've been waiting for,"},{"time":826621,"text":"and we have the chance to take that"},{"time":829083,"text":"and turn it into something which will, in fact,"},{"time":831573,"text":"knock out disease. That's my goal."},{"time":833903,"text":"I hope that's your goal."},{"time":835787,"text":"I think it'll be the goal of the poets and the muppets"},{"time":838467,"text":"and the surfers and the bankers"},{"time":840476,"text":"and all the other people who join this stage"},{"time":842754,"text":"and think about what we're trying to do here"},{"time":844504,"text":"and why it matters."},{"time":845669,"text":"It matters for now. It matters as soon as possible."},{"time":848439,"text":"If you don't believe me, just ask Sam."}]},{"cues":[{"time":851557,"text":"Thank you all very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":853000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}